HEADWORD: ACTH
<hw>ACTH</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a growth hormone produced
by the anterior pituitary gland; stimulates the adrenal
cortex.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> adrenocorticotropic hormone, adrenocorticotrophic
hormone, adrenocorticotropin, adrenocorticotrophin, corticotropin,
corticotrophin</syn>⟦br⟧
